"script": "Your pencil has been lying to you, because there's no lead inside it at all. First, a black mineral called graphite is crushed into fine powder and mixed with wet clay. Then this paste is squeezed through a tiny hole, forming long spaghetti-like strands. And these strands are baked in an oven until they turn hard and smooth. Next, they're laid into grooves cut in a slab of cedar wood, and a second slab is glued on top. Finally, the wood is sliced into individual pencils, painted bright yellow, and tipped with an eraser nobody actually asked for.",
